were picked.

00:01:13.480 --> 00:01:16.160
I think that the idea behind
this collection is that these

00:01:16.160 --> 00:01:19.550
are applications which really
embrace the design guidelines

00:01:19.550 --> 00:01:25.370
but also go beyond that and
really have that level above

00:01:25.370 --> 00:01:27.660
that adds the polish that
makes it a beautifully

00:01:27.660 --> 00:01:28.360
designed application.

00:01:28.360 --> 00:01:29.930
ROMAN NURIK: Absolutely.

00:01:29.930 --> 00:01:30.810
So let's see.

00:01:30.810 --> 00:01:34.650
So the collection from the blog
post that we posted about

00:01:34.650 --> 00:01:38.380
this collection talks a lot
about attention to detail.

00:01:38.380 --> 00:01:42.940
And it's not really about just
getting the 80% of the app or

00:01:42.940 --> 00:01:44.150
90% of the app looking great.

00:01:44.150 --> 00:01:47.460
It's really just adding that
final 10% of fit and finish

00:01:47.460 --> 00:01:49.790
and polish that, again, like
Nick said, goes above and

00:01:49.790 --> 00:01:54.000
beyond just following the
guidelines and really kind of

00:01:54.000 --> 00:01:56.550
stressing that every
single part of

00:01:56.550 --> 00:01:58.490
the app must be polished.

00:01:58.490 --> 00:02:01.240
And really, you have to think
about every single flow that

00:02:01.240 --> 00:02:03.790
the user would go through.

00:02:03.790 --> 00:02:07.400
And so these 11 apps we found
contain some of these

00:02:07.400 --> 00:02:10.400
masterfully crafted
design details.

00:02:10.400 --> 00:02:11.740
And so that's why these
were chosen.

00:02:11.740 --> 00:02:13.410
Obviously, this is
only 11 apps.

00:02:13.410 --> 00:02:17.110
There are tons more beautiful
apps out there on Google Play.

00:02:17.110 --> 00:02:20.910
This is just kind of the first
set, or I guess the first

00:02:20.910 --> 00:02:24.780
collection in this set,
in this series.

00:02:24.780 --> 00:02:28.190
You should expect more in the
future, in the coming

00:02:28.190 --> 00:02:31.040
different seasons, since this
is just the summer 2013

00:02:31.040 --> 00:02:33.940
collection.

00:02:33.940 --> 00:02:38.410
And we also wanted to mention
that very recently, there are

00:02:38.410 --> 00:02:40.000
some other apps that have
been published.

00:02:40.000 --> 00:02:44.400
And Matias Duarte, who's the
Director of User Experience

00:02:44.400 --> 00:02:49.990
for Android, had this really
long Google+ post that talked

00:02:49.990 --> 00:02:54.660
about kind of where the
guidelines sit in terms of the

00:02:54.660 --> 00:02:56.560
design process.

00:02:56.560 --> 00:02:59.330
How you should approach the
guidelines, what types of

00:02:59.330 --> 00:03:01.900
decisions you should be thinking
about, where you

00:03:01.900 --> 00:03:05.550
should begin introducing
branding and consistency and

00:03:05.550 --> 00:03:06.890
things like that.

00:03:06.890 --> 00:03:10.610
So while we're on the topic
of the Beautiful Design

00:03:10.610 --> 00:03:11.170
collection--

00:03:11.170 --> 00:03:14.130
which, again, the apps there do
follow the guidelines, but

00:03:14.130 --> 00:03:15.860
they go above and beyond that--
while we're on the

00:03:15.860 --> 00:03:19.660
topic of this, I think that this
post really summarizes

00:03:19.660 --> 00:03:23.070
some of the Android Design
team's views on the guidelines

00:03:23.070 --> 00:03:26.840
and consistency and
where they fit in.

00:03:26.840 --> 00:03:31.490
So with that, should we jump
in with the first app?

